 had a hard life and was used to bad news.\",\"index\":152,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"John Wiley did not call me for casual reasons. If he called, it was serious, possibly even deadly serious.\",\"index\":153,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"hierarchy\":[{\"content\":\"Ben: “Hello.”\",\"index\":154,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"John: “Ben, the office said not to bother you, but I just want to let you know that Felicia stopped breathing, but she is not going to die.”\",\"index\":155,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"Ben: “Not going to die? What?!?! What happened?”\",\"index\":156,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"I could not believe it. I had been so focused on work that I had lost focus of the only thing that really mattered to me. Once again, I neglected to worry about the one thing that I should have worried about.\",\"index\":157,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"Ben: “What happened?”\",\"index\":158,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"John: “They gave her some medicine and she had an allergic reaction and she stopped breathing, but she’s okay now.”\",\"index\":159,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"Ben: “When?”\",\"index\":160,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"John: “Yesterday.”\",\"index\":161,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"Ben: “What? Why didn’t you tell me?”\",\"index\":162,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"John: “I knew that you were busy and that you were really in trouble at work because of that meeting that I went to.”\",\"index\":163,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"Ben: “Should I come home?”\",\"index\":164,\"type\":\"markdown\",\"summarizable\":true},{\"content\":\"John: “Oh no. We’ll take care of her. You just take care of what you need to do.”